This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of database systems, specifically in the context of OLTP and social networking workloads. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Database). The paper also extensively uses machine learning techniques to develop intelligent scheduling algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of scheduling on system performance, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents empirical results and performance measurements, which could also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
